{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3f0f1496-d54a-470a-b944-28b5fbb5ec26","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Z8QKgkNix9RuXP3eu9mMtj","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-6a30168b30704f6299764806ce4ec65c/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-6a30168b30704f6299764806ce4ec65c/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"6f16935a-7ef9-4a66-a1ae-4a384ee65424","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` \n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `BrokenOrder.Domain` (it has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`), which is defined in `Domain.fs`. Since `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, the compiler can't find the `Domain` module when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs` (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both Domain and Services)","outputTokens":476,"requestId":"F021:C87BE:255CDF0:2960F13:69F93E27"},"id":"bba0a57f-4a09-41ba-b4d4-78d64fab6e61","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:43.362Z","parentId":"2a7d395a-d520-4784-95a8-2066635e41b9"}
